{"name": "harmonyhub-cli", "metadata": {"name": "harmonyhub-cli", "version": "0.0.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/rahgadda/HarmonyHub", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["jq", "PyYAML", "jinja2", "fastapi", "uvicorn"], "summary": "A CLI library for HarmonyHub", "upload_time": 1734085944}, "documentation": ["# HarmonyHub\r\n\r\n## Overview\r\n- This is a Visual API Orchestrator POC created for Rest API Calls.\r\n- UI Generates YAML. Written in static HTML using WebComponents. \r\n- Python-based `CLI` is used to run YAML generated from UI. It can sequence and execute API Calls.\r\n\r\n## Commands\r\n- harmonyhub init\r\n  - harmonyhub init --file workflow.yaml\r\n- harmonyhub run <<workflow.yaml>>\r\n  - pyyaml2apiworkflow run <<workflow.yaml>> --debug\r\n- harmonyhub --help\r\n- harmonyhub --version\r\n\r\n## Operator Supported\r\n- Simple comparisons (==, !=, >, <, >=, <=)\r\n- Logical operations (and, or, not)\r\n- Basic arithmetic operations (+, -, *, /, %)\r\n\r\n## Output Parser\r\n- [JQ](https://www.devtoolsdaily.com/jq_playground/)\r\n\r\n## System Defined Variables\r\n- $response\r\n- $request\r\n- $http_status\r\n\r\n## Roadmap\r\n- GraphQL\r\n- Grpc\r\n- Kafka\r\n\r\n## Demo\r\n- Demo created [here](https://app.beeceptor.com/console/automation-demo)\r\n\r\n## Credits\r\n- Below are projects used as inspiration\r\n  - [Stepci](https://stepci.com/)\r\n  - [Apache Karavan](https://github.com/apache/camel-karavan)\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "src.components", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "src", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "src.hmh_exception", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "src.hmh_exception.RestException", "bases": ["Exc